# 🍽️ Restaurant Menu Web App  

A fully responsive, real-time restaurant ordering web app built with **Supabase** and **vanilla JavaScript**.  
Customers can browse meals, add to cart, view categories, choose order type (Dine-in / Takeaway), and place orders directly via **WhatsApp**.  
The admin dashboard updates the frontend in **real time** — when meals are added, edited, or archived, the menu instantly updates without reloading.  

---

## 🚀 Features  

- ✅ **Dynamic Menu Display** — Meals fetched from Supabase and grouped by category  
- 🔁 **Real-time Sync** — Instantly reflects added, updated, or archived meals  
- 🛒 **Cart System** — Add, remove, or adjust items with live totals  
- 💬 **WhatsApp Order Flow** — Sends order summary directly to restaurant’s WhatsApp  
- 🌗 **Light/Dark Mode** — Theme toggle with persistent state  
- 🍔 **Category Tabs** — Filter meals instantly by category  
- ⚡ **Optimized Caching** — Faster load times via local caching  
- 📱 **Responsive Layout** — Works smoothly on mobile, tablet, and desktop  

---

## 🧩 Tech Stack  

| Layer | Technology |
|:------|:------------|
| **Frontend** | HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Vanilla JS) |
| **Backend** | [Supabase](https://supabase.com) — Database + Realtime |
| **Hosting** | [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com) |
| **Integration** | WhatsApp API for order messages |

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions  

### 1️⃣ Clone Repository  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO_NAME.git
cd YOUR_REPO_NAME
````

### 2️⃣ Configure Supabase

Create a new project on [Supabase](https://supabase.com) and add the following tables:

#### 🧾 `meals` Table

| Column      | Type      | Description              |
| :---------- | :-------- | :----------------------- |
| id          | uuid      | Primary key              |
| name        | text      | Meal name                |
| price       | numeric   | Price of the meal        |
| description | text      | Meal description         |
| image_url   | text      | Image link               |
| category    | text      | Meal category            |
| archived    | boolean   | Whether meal is hidden   |
| created_at  | timestamp | Auto-generated timestamp |

#### 🛍️ `orders` Table

| Column         | Type      | Description               |
| :------------- | :-------- | :------------------------ |
| customer_name  | text      | Customer’s name           |
| order_type     | text      | dine-in / takeaway        |
| items          | json      | Ordered items (array)     |
| total_amount   | numeric   | Total order cost          |
| payment_method | text      | cash / transfer           |
| status         | text      | pending / completed       |
| table_number   | text      | Table number (if dine-in) |
| created_at     | timestamp | Timestamp                 |

Then, replace the keys in your script:

```js
const SUPABASE_URL = 'https://YOUR_PROJECT_ID.supabase.co';
const SUPABASE_KEY = 'YOUR_PUBLIC_ANON_KEY';
```

---

### 3️⃣ Run Locally

Simply open `index.html` in your browser or use a local server (VS Code Live Server, etc.).

### 4️⃣ Deploy Online

Deploy the project using [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com) or [Vercel](https://vercel.com).
Upload both your **frontend (index2.html)** and **dashboard (admin.html)** files.

---

## 💬 WhatsApp Integration

Orders are sent directly to your WhatsApp.
To update your restaurant number, change this line in the script:

```js
window.open(`https://wa.me/234XXXXXXXXXX?text=${encodeURIComponent(waMessage)}`, '_blank');
```

---

## 🧠 Developer Notes

* Archiving a meal in the admin panel hides it from the menu **in real time**.
* Adjust caching duration inside your JS file:

  ```js
  const CACHE_DURATION = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes
  ```
* Real-time updates handled by Supabase:

  ```js
  supabase
    .channel('public:meals')
    .on('postgres_changes', { event: '*', schema: 'public', table: 'meals' }, loadMeals)
    .subscribe();
  ```

